FAQ
Q: What evidence supports HydraFacial efficacy?
A: Peer-reviewed studies on hydradermabrasion-style treatments consistently show short-term improvements in skin hydration, texture, and pore appearance. Long-term structural benefits require further controlled study.

Q: Is HydraFacial standardised across providers?
A: The core device and protocol are standardised, but serum selection, treatment intensity, and practitioner skill introduce variability. Provider competency significantly affects outcomes.

Q: Can HydraFacial be combined with other treatments?
A: Yes, commonly with LED phototherapy, dermaplaning, or low-level radiofrequency. Combination with injectables or laser procedures requires spacing and practitioner coordination.
